# Nebius 
CW of Europe; focus on open source rather than proprietary nature of CW agenda. Introduced "Token Factory" in November 2025 to host over 60 leading open-source models (incl. deepseek, llama, qwen, nvidia nemotron etc.), using an openAI-compatible API (devs can easily swap out proprietary models such as chatgpt for open-source models hosted by Nebius.). Token Factory is also for post-training to customize open-weight models with specific data (fine-tuning, distillation). 
Fine-Tuning: You can use your own proprietary datasets to fine-tune models (using methods like LoRA or full supervised fine-tuning) so they match your company's tone, adhere to your domain-specific terminology, or output strict formats like JSON or SQL.
Distillation: This is a major feature of the platform. It allows users to take a massive, expensive "teacher" model and compress its knowledge into a smaller "student" model. The result is a custom model that runs 3 to 5 times faster and costs significantly less to operate, while maintaining high reasoning quality

